      "title": "Apply input phase: pPhases[u] & 0xF = 0x01 → negate x0",
      "narrative": "The low 4 bits of <code>pPhases[u]</code> are an input-phase mask: bit k set means input <code>x_k</code> is negated. Here only bit 0 is set — feed <code>¬x0</code> into the slot that originally received <code>x0</code>.<br><br>Visually: the canonical edge from x0 was <em>dashed</em> (canonical wanted <code>¬x0</code>). Composing the edge polarity with the new input negation gives <em>solid</em> (¬¬x0 = x0). The slot label flips to <code>¬x0</code> to record the binding.",
